ake specific actions and cited loebs letter to sevin as exemplary of the genre noting that three weeks after the letter was sent sevin was gone and a jubilant mr loeb sent out an email message to friends and associates declaring a huge victory for third point personal lifeedit loeb married margaret davidson munzer on july   at his beach house in east hampton new york the couple has three children loeb is a founding master player of portfolios with purpose an annual virtual stock trading contest that raises money for charitable causes of the winning contestants choice loeb has called himself a lifelong surfer with a secret spot in the caribbean his second favorite surfing spot is in indonesia third point takes its name from a break at malibus surfrider beach in  loeb was reported as one of a number of prominent investors who have taken to transcendental meditation loeb was cochair of the governors for investors industry  he is a trustee of mount sinai hospital the manhattan institute the us olympic committee and the los angeles museum of contemporary art he is a member of the council on foreign relations and of the national council of the american enterprise institute political and economic viewsedit loeb has donated to the democratic senatorial campaign committee friends for harry reid obama for america forward together pac prosperity pac straight talk america and the volunteer pac in  loeb was a signatory to an amicus curiae brief submitted to the us supreme court in hollingsworth v perry in support of samesex marriage in  loeb paul singer and tim gill helped fund freedom for all americans to promote lgbt issues in states and local communities in the united states wealth and philanthropyedit according to forbes magazine his net worth is  billion usd as of february  the daniel s loeb family third point foundationedit the daniel s loeb family third point foundation earned  million in profits in  and had  billion in assets at the end of that year making it one of the largest and highestearning private foundations its nonprofit administrative expense ratio a measure of its operating and administrating expenses was  compared to the  average of  for all private foundations loeb is heavily involved in education reform efforts specifically supporting charter schools loeb is chairman of the board of success academy charter schools in brooklyn in june  he pledged to donate  million to success academy charter schools he endowed the daniel s loeb scholarship for undergraduate study at columbia university since  he has been a trustee of prep for prep an organization in new york city that prepares underprivileged children to attend competitive private schools he is active in the jewish enrichment center which provides young people with an education in judaism additionally he is a cofounder of students first new york the state branch of the national education advocacy organization on february   loeb attended a discussion between the american enterprise institute and the dalai lama the two worldviews debated the morality of capitalism and free enterprise in loebs presentation he said he practices ashtanga yoga and applies yoga principles to his business and his decisionmaking he noted that these principles aided in his decision to donate to a charter school in the bronx which is now ranked third in the state of new york in october  loeb challenged three former navy seals to run the mightyman half iron triathlon with him and his team in montauk new york he made a sizable contribution for each navy seal foundation director who completed the triathlon to raise funds for the foundation in   and  loeb and his wife made significant donations to the alzheimers drug discovery foundation addf which funds over  alzheimers drug discovery programs in academic centers and biotechnology companies in  different countries loeb and his wife have also donated to the leukemia and lymphoma society ovarian cancer research fund chai lifeline and the michael j fox foundation art collectionedit he is a prominent art collector and the walls at his park avenue office are covered with paintings according to a new york times august   article at a sothebys auction in  manhattan dealer larry gagosian purchased jeff koons baroque egg with bow turquoisemagenta for  million from loeb who had bought it from the gagosian gallery in  for about  million loeb has traced his love of art to his student years at columbia when he saw poussins the rape of the sabine women at the metropolitan museum of art and took an art humanities class as part of the core curriculum the prep school kids treated him like a jerk thinking they all knew so much more but in the end i got one of two as and all the prep school snotty kids didnt business insider placed loeb at the top of its list of wall streets  most serious art collectors noting he owns works by mike kelley richard prince basquiat andy warhol and cindy sherman and that he “has his own curator” referencesedit  dan loeb bio returns net worth insider monkey retrieved  june    third point – about us third point llc retrieved may     a b c d e f g h fishman steve get richest quickest new york magazine retrieved october     oleinic alex  march  why you should follow billionaire dan loebs smallcap picks seeking alpha retrieved  april    a b c d weddingscelebrations margaret munzer daniel loeb new york times july   retrieved august    a b c d gopinath deepak hedgefund rabble rouser bloomberg markets october  retrieved august    kampeas ron jewish republican progay rights archived december   at the wayback machine jta may    a b c la roche julia the fabulous life of dan loeb – the hedge fund manager at war against bill ackman business insider retrieved october     a b bailey brandon daniel loeb southern california native a hedge fund manager who takes on corporate executives silicon valley may   retrieved may    a b c daniel loeb profile at salt conference retrieved october     la roche julia he didnt alway